-- ABB Units Charged With Breaking U.S. Law in Corruption, Oil-For-Food Cases
-- B y   A n d r e w   M .   H a r r i s
-- 2010-09-29T19:29:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/abb-units-charged-with-breaking-u-s-law-in-corruption-oil-for-food-cases.html
Two units of ABB Ltd., the Swiss
engineering firm, were charged by U.S. authorities today. One
was accused of violating the Foreign Corrupt Practices Act; the
other faces a conspiracy charge involving the United Nations
oil-for-food program with Iraq.  To contact the reporter on this story:
